.TH "SIMPLE_SHELL" 1 "26/4/2026" "1.0" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.br
.B echo "command" | ./hsh
.br
.B ./hsh < file

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple shell that reads commands from standard input, executes them, and
waits for more input until the shell is exited or end-of-file is reached.

When run with standard input connected to a terminal, the shell runs in
interactive mode and displays a prompt before each command.

When input is piped or redirected into the shell, it runs in non-interactive
mode and executes the given input without displaying a prompt.

.SH OPTIONS
This shell does not support command line options.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.

.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.

.TP
.B setenv VARIABLE VALUE
Create or update an environment variable.

.TP
.B unsetenv VARIABLE
Remove an environment variable.

.TP
.B cd [DIRECTORY]
Change the current working directory.

.SH COMMANDS
If the input is not a built-in command, the shell attempts to execute it as an
external program.

Commands may be executed from the current directory or found using the
.B PATH
environment variable.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B Interactive mode
.RS
./hsh
.br
$ ls
.br
$ pwd
.br
$ echo hello
.br
$ exit
.RE

.TP
.B Non-interactive mode
.RS
echo "ls" | ./hsh
.RE

.TP
.B Run commands from a file
.RS
./hsh < commands.txt
.RE

.TP
.B Print environment
.RS
env
.RE

.TP
.B Set an environment variable
.RS
setenv NAME value
.RE

.TP
.B Remove an environment variable
.RS
unsetenv NAME
.RE

.TP
.B Change directory
.RS
cd /tmp
.RE

